The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Sept. 7: The government today said it had initiated prosecutions against 107 fraudulent companies and their promoters and directors under the Companies Act, 1956. The government has launched prosecutions against 94 companies for non-filing of statutory returns. The cases are pending before different high courts for decision, an official statement said. FIRs have been filed against 100 companies. 

 New Delhi, Sept. 7: The Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI) will come out with its second accounting standards on computation and certification of the fringe benefit tax in one-and-a-half months. ICAI has already issued its first guidance note on accounting of FBT in the book of accounts.

 New Delhi, Sept. 7: The Centre?s gross market borrowings rose by 62 per cent to Rs 89,000 crore till September 2 compared with Rs 55,000 crore during the same period last year, PNB Gilts said in a report. It will raise Rs 8,000 crore tomorrow.

 Calcutta, Sept. 7: Balmer Lawrie has shortlisted five consultants, of which one will be selected for reviewing the company?s strategic plan. The company will invite expressions of interest from Mckinsey, Accenture, Ernst amp; Young, PricewaterhouseCoopers, Boston Consulting Group and Eicher Consultancy Services.

 New Delhi, Sept. 7: Oil and Natural Gas Corporation has received government approval for building a Rs 7,967-crore refinery at Barmer district of Rajasthan, chairman Subir Raha said.




